detailedRequirements:
Task Overview

The goal  of this challenge is to create a Contact Us page for each minisite following the Contact Us page UI from mainsite.

Task Requirements

  • Attached UI Prototypes in the forums for main site and minisites, you need to add contact us page in each minisite that matches the mainsite page
  • Some notes to be added to the pages :
    • Circuitbot
      • Contact Us widget title should be changed to <h1> CircuitBot: Contact us for assistance with our robot colony game </h1> The styling should be remain as it is after changing span to head tag.
      • Change the following to use h2 tag instead of span
        • Play For Free
        • Bring your friends ..
        • Protect Our Interent!
    • Xylem
      • Contact Us widget title should be changed to <h1> Xylem: Get support for our free botanical puzzle adventure</h1> The styling should be remain as it is after changing span to head tag.
      • Change the following to use h2 tag instead of span

        • Bring your friends ..
        • Protect Our Interent!
    • Flowjam
      • Contact Us widget title should be changed to <h1> Flow Jam: Get in touch for help with the electric puzzle game </h1> The styling should be remain as it is after changing span to head tag.
      • Change the following to use h2 tag instead of span

        • Protect Our Interent!
    • Ghostmap
      • Contact Us widget title should be changed to <h1> Ghost Map: Get in touch for help with our neural network game </h1> The styling should be remain as it is after changing span to head tag.
      • Change the following to use h2 tag instead of span
        • Play For Free

        • Protect Our Interent!
    • Stormbound
      • Contact Us widget title should be changed to <h1> StormBound: Get help with our tangled pattern puzzles</h1> The styling should be remain as it is after changing span to head tag.
      • Change the following to use h2 tag instead of span
        • Play For Free

  • The contact us page MUST match the production, the ui prototype in verigames folder is identical but there are slight differences, so we want to take production version.
